 KILLING THEIR OWN EVIL DEITIES in preference to taking down targets like Tunare or the other good/neutral deities. <br><br>Now don't get me wrong.... I totally understand that some epic items can only be obtained by raiding the evil planes like Fear or Hate. That's an understandable reason. <br><br>What I don't understand is that ever since Verant introduced some of the &quot;goodlier&quot; planes like Tunare's Plane of Growth.... the overwhelming number of guilds (both good and evil designated ones) still overwhelmingly choose to organize raids based on the fact that it's much more convenient to kill evil gods like Cazic in Fear and Inny in Hate. <br><br>Let's take a theoretical example. I'm a necromancer of Bertoxxulous. I'm a role player. I like to RP evil, perhaps not as strongly as other players....but I do prefer to stay in character when possible. <br><br>When the time for my epics and such comes.... I find out that I can obtain ALL my epics without needing to raid Bertoxxulous and his Plane (I'm not sure if its active yet) <br><br>So I ask myself.... why the heck should I even participate in a raid against my own god if I were to be invited in such a raid??? <br><br>As role player I would consider that a totally repulsive idea!!  Slaying my own deity when there is no pragmatic reason to do so.... other than the lust and greed for phat lewt.... is a distasteful idea to me. <br><br>So what happens when my GuildMaster says: <br><br>&quot;Maladominus, you are an ass.... we really needed you to help us out in the raid against Bertox, but you refused to come along for role playing reasons. Please leave the guild ASAP.&quot;<br><br>So now what? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br>Please folks, I would appreciate your input, wether you agree with me or disagree with me. I have not yet guilded.... but this is an important issue with me when the time comes. <br><br>And please remember the title: Evil Role Playing Guilds!  This scrutiny does NOT apply to you if you belong to a non-RP guild. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>P.S. -- I posted this in general forum because I am not making a call for a guild, nor am I soliciting for one at this moment. I am asking for feedback.... especially since this is an issue for both role players and powergamers alike. <br><br>For intelligent responses..... /applaud<br><br>For incoming flames...... /rude <br><br>Bring it on! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br><br>--<br>Maladominus Poxbringer<br>Sexy Gnecromancer <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=milosh>Milosh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/23/02 3:45:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1174.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Evil RP Guilds focus on killing GOOD deities?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> So what happens when my GuildMaster says: <br><br>&quot;Maladominus, you are an ass.... we really needed you to help us out in the raid against Bertox, but you refused to come along for role playing reasons. Please leave the guild ASAP.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>I'm confused, are you in a Roleplaying guild?  What kind of RP guildmaster would ever punish someone for roleplaying?  Sounds like this guildmaster needs a swift kick to the jimmy before you quit his ridiculous guild. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Iksar Fanatic</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/23/02 4:06:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1174.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Evil RP Guilds focus on killing GOOD deities?</span><hr size=1> Well, Cazic-Thule actually doesn't mind it when Iksar raid his plane so long as they don't kill him. He cons warmly to Iksar and the only way to change that is to kill him. Iksar would have no problem with raiding the plane of Hate seeing as Innoruuk is just as much their enemy as Tunare. Verant also once said that Innoruuk would be proud if his children hated him so much that they tried to kill him, so actually raiding hate is an all around okay thing for everyone to do.<br><br>The reason people don't go after Tunare is actually because Tunare is I hear much MUCH harder to kill then the other gods, and I hear she dropped horrendously crappy loot. So it's generally just not worth the effort and time it takes to kill such a powerful foe. I heard that they improved her loot but she's still VERY hard to kill. I'd love to kill her sometime though, but I don't think I'll ever get the chance. Oh well. <br><br>Zildrax Shathrais <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/23/02 4:12:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1174.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Evil RP Guilds focus on killing GOOD deities?</span><hr size=1> Milosh <br><br>That's my entire point. On the previous servers I've played on.... many guilds BEGIN their foundation as a so-called evil-oriented RPing guild. But in the later levels, they become sellouts.... they gradually forsake any RP house rules they may have for the ability to rake in PHAT LEWT from any and all types of raids..... regardless of what they kill or who they kill. <br><br>The reason I bring this up now is because hardly any (or maybe a couple at most) guilds are of uber caliber yet on this server..... but there will come a time when many of the RP-ing guilds on this server will become epic-capable.... and then thats when this will become an issue....... that may tear people apart. <br><br>I do appreciate your sentiment....I would feel the same way if my guildmaster chastised me for sticking to my role playing ideals. <br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A> at: 1/23/02 4:17:08 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utukka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tukka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/23/02 4:17:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1174.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.atlantic.net/~tukka/hand.gif height=42 width=42></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Evil RP Guilds focus on killing GOOD deities?</span><hr size=1> Well, one thing to remember about evil is that it is generally defined by one's lack of morality, virtue, honor (or whatever word you want to use).  In virtually every work of fiction I've read (and many non-fictional historical accounts), &quot;evil&quot; individuals are indeed &quot;sell outs&quot;.  They will betray their friends, their leaders, even their religion and their gods if it suits them.<br><br>Is it a betrayal of one's god to stand against them and fight their other minions?  Perhaps, but I think it's a lot easier for an evil character to rationalize his fight against his own god and his own god's minions, based on just what those gods are the gods OF--Hate, Fear, War, Death.  By allowing themselves to be consumed (and consuming others with them) by these things in a raid on their deity's plane, are they not simultaneously honoring their god, even as they make an attempt to destroy that god and his local minions?<br><br>I would agree that dark characters would make an obvious enemy of light characters and deities of Light (though right now the only &quot;Good&quot; deity you can kill is Tunare, and she's a toughy by all accounts).<br><br>I think there enough ways to explain/rationalize raiding one's own deity's plane for evil guilds... and obviously, it was part of Verant's &quot;vision&quot; to have evil characters killing their own god (evident in the fact that shadow knights have to raid both the planes of Hate and Fear to get their weapon, and the fact that you don't get negative faction hits for Innoruuk/Cazic worshipping factions for doing so).<br><br>Now, a supposed roleplay guild kicking out a character for not participating in a raid (for roleplay purposes) would just be stupid.  If the guild can't raid an area because a couple people don't want to fight their own god, then they probably shouldn't be trying to raid that area anyway... and if they can raid those areas with a couple people opting out for RP reasons, they ought to respect that decision and let them stay in the guild.<br> <p><FONT FACE="Comic Sans MS">--Tukka</FONT><BR>EverQuest characters:<BR>Tukka (Brell Serilis)<BR>Velsor (Firiona Vie)<BR>