...I'm thinking not, but I've never looked at one of those spoiler sites just to find out how to do my epic... (I should probably do that just in case something trivials out).<br><br>Here's my thoughts.  Any guildmaster that would kick you out of the guild because you refuse to do a raid isn't worthy of your time.  He obviously doesn't care about you as a person, and I don't think anyone, guild or not, should be commanded to play any certain way.  You have a real life, you may have other things interfering with coming to a raid.  Surely they wouldn't kick you out if you missed it?<br><br>So what's the difference in that you refuse to partake?  Sure, they're less one necro, but big whoop.  Chances are that if you aren't interested in the uber loot, and they are to the point of throwing off all RP, then they aren't exactly what you're looking for.  Myself, I'd leave them.<br><br>Still, there are certain reasons why one might kill his own god.  Take the story of Lanys T'vyl.  She attempted to repiece the sword Malevolence, which weakens Innoruuk with every death it takes, just so she could kill Innoruuk and take his place.  And she is his own daughter.  So why shouldn't dark elves try to kill him, to assume their rightful place as Lord of Hate?<br><br>I don't see why any Cazicite would want to kill Cazic-Thule, except for the Trolls as they were abandoned in favor of the Iksar.  They could have some vengeance issues playing.<br><br>And hell.  I'd try to kill Tunare, if my RP guild decided they wanted to do it, phat lewt or no.  It's RP.  Imagine the fun I'd have walking around telling all the lowbies how my guild and I smacked around their god. <p><center><font size=+2><a href="http://pub66.ezboard.com/bmaidensfancy">Shiden Kaidan</a></font><br>Tier'dal Knight<br><a href="http://www.firiona-vie.com/"> Firiona Vie</a><br><font size=1><font color=red>@}</font><font color=green>--,--'---- </font></font><br><i>"You have no power over me."</i></center></p><